My personal solution is along the same lines, but much less global and annoying. This is in my .bash_profile:<p># todo
function todo {
	case &quot;$1&quot; in
		&quot;-a&quot;)
			echo &quot;$2&quot; >> $HOME/.todo
			;;
		&quot;-d&quot;)
			sed -i &quot;&quot; -e &quot;$2d&quot; $HOME/.todo
			;;
	esac
	if [ -f &quot;$HOME/.todo&quot; ] ; then
		cat $HOME/.todo | awk &#x27;{ print NR, &quot;-&quot;, $0 }&#x27;
	fi
}
